More than 15,000 children under the age of 5 have already been vaccinated against measles in the Drakenstein &amp;Stellenbosch areas. CAPE TOWN The Western Cape Health Department says it is taking its mass vaccination campaign against measles to all areas in the province.More than 15,000 children under the age of 5 have already been vaccinated against measles in the Drakenstein and Stellenbosch areas.The department launched its campaign at the start of February following an outbreak of measles at several schools in these areas.Health officials in the public and private sector have been requested to be on the look-out for measles symptoms in patients, and to report it immediately to the department.The department's Jo-Anne Otto said, As of next week children between the ages of 6 and 59 months will be vaccinated. Parents should visit clinics rather than wait for us. 